results.title: Live Laugh Love | Typographic Print
results.description:
LIVE LAUGH LOVE PRINT

Contemporary meets vintage in this inspirational quote print.  Bold, modern headings are embellished with Victorian script and flourishes to create a classically clean print that will sit comfortably in both traditional and modern settings.  

Did you know...? This popular quote is an adaptation of the first line of a poem titled "What Is Success?" which was written in 1904 by Bessie Anderson Stanley for a Boston magazine competition. The first line read: "He has achieved success who has lived well, laughed often and loved much." Bessie won the first prize of $250. Go girl! 

DIMENSIONS:

A4 print size: 30 cm high x 21 cm wide
A3 print size: 42 cm high x 30 cm wide

PRINT INFO:

All our unique designs are printed using long-lasting inks on museum-quality fine art paper that is lovingly made in the UK with a natural white finish and slightly textured surface... which means that you'll receive a vibrantly rich print that looks good, feels good and will last a lifetime.
 
Please note that our prints do not come framed and are shown in frames for illustrative and inspirational purposes only. Actual printed colours may vary slightly from how they appear on screen.
 
DELIVERY:

Delivery is free within the UK. 
A4 prints are sent in double hardbacked envelopes by first class post.
A3 prints are rolled in acid-free tissue and sent in sturdy cardboard tubes by first class post.
All orders are dispatched within 48 hours of ordering.
